  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison is relieved to hear that sister Sarah is with Helen Eliza Garrison. He appreciates the &quot;sisterly kindness&quot; of Mrs. Garnaut and Miss Cannan. Garrison is uneasy about Wendell Phillips&apos;s health; he wishes that Wendell Phillips had faith in the water cure. Garrison discusses his children, family, and domestic matters.</subfield>
